hought.\n\n- Kathryn Stockett, The Help\n|\nThe universe evolved from something and nothing, and has most of these elemental dualpair until now.\n\n- Joey\n|\nOf all sad words of tongue or pen, the saddest are these, 'It might have been.\n\n- John Greenleaf Whittier, Maud Muller - Pamphlet\n|\nA writer needs a partner who can act as fuel to his artistic mind, yet has the great ability to sober him up and help him be in sync with the non-artistic part of his soul.\n\n- Janvier\n|\nWhen a woman rises up in glory, her energy is magnetic and her sense of possibility contagious.\n\n- Marianne Williamson, A Woman's Worth\n|\nThe paper landed on the table, but the news was stapled to his chest. A tattoo.\n\n- Markus Zusak, The Book Thief\n|\nYour on your on with this one babe.''Coward.''Calling me names isn't going to get me in there.'-Ranger and Stephanie\n\n- Janet Evanovich, To the Nines\n|\nWhen you handle books all day long, every new one is a friend and a temptation.\n\n- Elizabeth Kostova, The Historian\n|\nRome wasn’t built in a day, but that's because they never used Cosmic Ordering.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering: You can be successful\n|\nShut up!' Eve yelled from somewhere upstairs. 'Jackass!''You know, when people say that, I just hear the word awesome,\n\n- Rachel Caine, Last Breath\n|\nThe truth about life and lie about life is not measured by others but by your intuition, which never lies.\n\n- Santosh\n|\nA spoon does not know the taste of soup, nor a learned fool the taste of wisdom.\n\n- Anonymous\n|\nAnd I meant to tell you: that was a one-in-a-thousand shot.'She raised her hand. 'Don't.''It was awesome,' George confirmed. 'It really was,' Jack said. 'His head exploded.\n\n- Ilona Andrews, Fate's Edge\n|\nThe most important thing in life is to learn how to give out love, and let it come in.\n\n- Morrie\n|\nIf we read the Word of God, we shall know the will of God.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nAs the fear of God is the beginning of wisdom, so the denial of Go